homepage_content: Museum of the Great Southern | Western Australian Museum Skip to main content Museum of the Great Southern Residency Road, Albany What's on Exhibitions Visit us Residency Road, Albany, WA, 6330 Get directions on Google Maps > Plan your journey by public transport > Opening hours Open daily 10am – 4pm Public holiday hours Anzac Day 1pm – 4pm Closed Christmas Day, Boxing Day, New Year's Day & Good Friday General Admission Free General Admission entry Donations are welcome Some special exhibitions and events may charge a fee Information for educators > Contact us (08) 9841 4844 reception@museum.wa.gov.au ‌‌ ‌‌ ‌‌ ‌‌ @wamuseum Accessibility The Museum of the Great Southern is mostly accessible A lift is available for access to the mezzanine floor in the Eclipse gallery space, but not for access to the Brig Amity More about accessibility and amenities > Explore the unique natural and social history of the Great Southern region. The Museum of the Great Southern precinct overlooks picturesque Mamang Koort / Princess Royal Harbour on the site of the first European permanent settlement in Western Australia (1826). Here you will find permanent and travelling exhibitions, a replica of the Brig Amity , pop-up artworks, public and educational programs, and information on the natural and social history of the region. The Museum shares the stories of the Menang Noongar people and the influence of Mokare, an intermediary who assisted European explorers in an unfamiliar environment. It also explores the region's unique landscapes, flora and fauna. What's on at Museum of the Great Southern Special exhibitions Men of the Kokoda Explore the story of Brigadier Arnold Potts and the 21st Brigade of the Second AIF, whose actions during the defence of the Kokoda Trail during WWII became some of the most debated in Australia’s military history. Resources Explore the history of the Great Southern with these resources from the Western Australian Museum. More information to help plan your visit Accessibility and amenities Access within Museum All galleries have level flooring. Level 2 of the Eclipse building is only accessible via elevator. ACROD Parking Main Museum carpark. Two large bays available. Level access. No barriers. Free (no cost). Audio Guides Available on the Brig Amity . Captioning Not available. Drop Off Area Main Museum carpark. Drop off in front of Eclipse Building or Residency Building. Level access. No barriers. Entry to Museum Accessible path from parking and drop off area to Museum entry. Small ramp leading down to Eclipse Building entrance, small ramp leading up to Co-op Building and School Room. No stairs to either main entrances. All entrances level. All doors manual opening. Equipment Available One manual wheelchair available for use. Hearing Loops No hearing loops available. Reception The reception desk is located in the Eclipse Building on the ground floor, immediately inside the doors. Share Paths The Museum is central located in Albany and easily accessible by walkers and cyclists using Albany’s extensive network of Share Paths. The Albany TravelSmart Map shows all the available paths. Albany TravelSmart Map [PDF 2MB] Storage Please be aware that the Museum of the Great Southern does not have cloaking facilities or bag storage areas. As a consequence, luggage and bags should not be taken into the Museum. Toilets The site does not have universal access toilets. If required urgently, there is access to a larger, handled toilet within the staff administration area. Trained Guide or Assistance Dogs Visitors accompanied by a Trained Guide or Assistance Dog or a dog undergoing such training are welcome in this site. Getting here, public transport and parking Address Museum of the Great Southern Residency Road, Albany, Western Australia, 6330, Australia Get directions on Google Maps > By Car Parking is available in onsite. homepage_content: Home - Spinifex Motel & Serviced Apartments - Mt Isa 07 4749 2944 admin@spinifexmotel.com.au Slide Welcome to Spinifex Motel & Serviced Apartments - Mt Isa, QLD The Spinifex motel was specifically designed by its owner who had travelled extensively throughout Queensland, NSW, the Northern Territory and Western Australia for more than thirty years. He incorporated all the features he believed a motel should have to provide the best accommodation for the business traveller to feal relaxed and at home. Added to this he has appointed managers that are down to earth people who would cater to the needs of our guests with a ready smile. As Mt Isa's newest accommodation, Spinifex Motel & Serviced Apartments is equipped with modern facilities including LCD TV's, DVD players, Austar and our licenced Maggie's Bar. Coupled with the very best in hospitality, Spinifex Motel & Serviced Apartments is the perfect accommodation solution in Mount Isa. Privately owned and not part of chain, we specialise in personalising your stay. This coupled with its convenient location makes it ideal for the corporate traveller or holiday maker. We are only 3 minutes from the train station and 10 minutes from the airport. Whether you're staying for business or pleasure, Spinifex Motel & Serviced Apartments has a room to suit you. We offer executive rooms, deluxe rooms, adjoining rooms and disabled access rooms. Comfortable Rooms All our rooms are spotlessly clean and feature reverse cycle air-conditioning High Speed Internet Ideally suited to the traveling worker Reception Hours Our reception desk is open from 7:30am to 8:00pm every day Our Available Rooms The motel has 34 large executive King & Queen rooms including 2 Disabled & 2 Family rooms which can sleep up to 2 adults and 2 children. All rooms have a kitchenette, LCD Tvs, Foxtel, Free Wifi & Aircon. Rooms are serviced daily and are supplied with a range of complimentary amenities. homepage_content: Harvest Ministry of Food – Harvest Ministry of Food Skip to content Food Pantry Make an appointment Book now 5331 5957 Appointments available: Tuesday 1pm - 2pm Wednesday - 1pm - 3pm Thursday - 10am -12pm Thursday - 1pm - 3pm Contact for more information office@hilltop.church Harvest Ministry of Food We provide fruit and vegetables, frozen meals and pantry items to people in Ballarat effected by food insecurity. Whether you need a hand up while finding work, experiencing hardship with an influx of bills coming through or feeling the pinch with rising costs of living, when the question is 'what is for dinner?' we want to be part of an answer for you. Book now One of our friendly staff in the office at Hilltop.Church will answer your call and they will ask some simple questions to gauge your current situation. If you get the answering machine, please leave your name and contact number and the reason you are calling. When a time is booked, we'll let you know where the address is and what to expect. We offer a 30-minute booking where you may stay for a cuppa, a sandwich or a cup of hot soup. Here we'll get to know you and your needs, and help plan a food relief program that suits your needs. name: my.darwin.nt.gov.au
homepage_content: myDarwin | City of Darwin | Darwin Council, Northern Territory Skip to main content The myDarwin program is currently closed. City of Darwin thanks you for your participation of the initiative. The myDarwin economic stimulus is an initiative to provide support to local businesses and community residents through digital discounts. It was designed for local businesses in retail, tourism, and hospitality who were affected by closures, social distancing measures, and restricted hours of trade-related to the COVID-19 pandemic. myDarwin success in a snapshot As of April 2022, the myDarwin program has completed 10 rounds of funding which resulted to an average 5.7 multiplier effect into the local economy. Key statistics to date are: 476 Merchant registrations 343 Approved Merchants 54,433 User registrations 141,491 Discounts Redeemed $1,750,000 Funded Discounts $9,906,948 Economic Spend in local Businesses (x5.7 multiplied spend) Due to its success the Northern Territory Government has provided $1 million in funding for the myDarwin web application to be extended to other councils in the Northern Territory. This resulted in the creation of a white label version of myDarwin web application which can be used independently by other councils. The following councils have rebranded and implemented their version of myDarwin with shared success. In the Northern Territory: Alice Springs Council Palmerston Council Litchfield Council Katherine Council Barkly Regional Council In the Australian Capital Territory: Canberra’s ACT Government Discover more interesting facts about the myDarwin success and economic impact in YourDARWIN platform. homepage_content: Botanic Gardens | Cairns Regional Council Botanic Gardens Share Facebook Send In Messenger Send In Messenger Twitter Email The Cairns Botanic Gardens is a tropical paradise, renowned as one of the best exhibitions of tropical plants in Australia. Come and explore the beauty of tropical plants, relax in stunning surroundings and learn about tropical flora and horticulture. Christmas period operating hours The Flecker Botanic Gardens will remain open throughout the Christmas period, and will be open daily from 7.30am to 5.30pm. The Botanic Gardens Visitor Centre will be closed on Christmas Day. It will be open from 9.30am to 2pm on each day from 26 December to 1 January inclusive. Usual opening hours (8.30am to 4pm weekdays and 9.30am to 2pm weekends) will resume on 2 January 2025. The Gardens will remain open throughout the Christmas period. The Flecker Garden will be open daily from 7.30am to 5.30pm. Garden tours: resume Monday 24 February 2025 Bird walks : resume Tuesday 25 February 2025. Plant trolley sales: resume Wednesday 5 February 2025. Heritage Tours : Last tour 12 December 2024, resume 6 March 2025. Friends Shop (Flecker Garden) : closed from 20 December 2024, reopen Monday 13 January (mornings only) Opening hours Flecker Gardens, including Watkins Munro Martin Conservatory, open every day from 7.30am to 5.30pm (subject to weather conditions). All other garden areas are open around the clock. Botanic Gardens Visitor Centre open 8.30am to 4pm weekdays, 9.30am to 2pm weekends and public holidays. No animals are allowed in any part of the Cairns Botanic Gardens (including the Centenary Lakes area), however registered assistance animals are accepted. You may be asked to provide evidence that your dog is a legitimate assistance animal. So please ensure you bring appropriate evidence. Phone 4032 6650 for enquiries Admission is FREE Location Collins Avenue, Edge Hill. The Freshwater and Saltwater Lakes can be easily accessed from Greenslopes Street. On-street parking available along Collins Avenue and Greenslopes Street. Sunbus stops on Collins Avenue directly outside Flecker Gardens. Download a map ( PDF, 0.89 MB ) showing the key features and areas. Wheelchair / pram access: some paths in Flecker Garden are not suitable for wheelchairs and prams. The remainder of the gardens, including Centenary Lakes, is fully accessible. Download the accessibility map ( PDF, 3.57 MB ) or view the accessibility map on-screen ( JPG, 0.94 MB ) to identify areas where carer assist is required and areas that are not accessible. Visit the Gardens Visitor information centre, library, food and volunteer opportunities. Garden areas & collections From the Aboriginal Plant Use Garden to the Zhanjiang Friendship Garden, there's so much to explore in the Cairns Botanic Gardens. One visit is just not enough! Walking tours Discover more about the plants and animals in the Cairns Botanic Gardens on one of our free tours! Events & functions The Cairns Botanic Gardens is the perfect place to hold your next family function or corporate even Birds of the Gardens Come for the flowers, stay for the birds! The Cairns Botanic Gardens is known for its gorgeous plants but beautiful birds also abound here. Little Taccas Fortnightly, nature-based activity program for children under five. Features art and craft, storytelling, sing-alongs and garden discovery walks. Little Sprouts Registrations are open for the Term 4 Little Sprouts program. This program fills quickly so register now so you don’t miss out. homepage_content: Veterinary Clinic | Greencross Vets Southport Search for: Search Book Online Find Your Local Greencross Vet Healthy Pets Plus Emergency Services Preventive Care Wellness Dental Checks Parasites Microchipping Vaccinations Blood Tests Medical Care Surgery Desexing Digital X-Ray Ultrasound Clinical Pathology Knowledge & Advice Puppy School Kitten School Nutrition Weight Pet Health Parasite Prevention Flea Prevention Giardia Tick Prevention Zoonotic Diseases Intestinal Worming Heartworm Prevention Common Diseases Dental Disease Diabetes Melitis Kidney Disease Arthritis Common Conditions Bladder Stones Diarrhoea Ear Infections Hip Dysplasia Itchy Skin Vomiting Luxating Patella Pet Articles Dogs Dog Articles Puppy Articles Senior Dog Articles Cats Kitten Articles Cat Articles Senior Cat Articles Other Pets Pocket Pet Articles Bird Articles Careers Careers Vet Nurse Careers Vet Nurse Practical Pathway International Vets Total Care Loyalty Pet Sitting Hello, from Greencross Vets Southport Welcome to Greencross Vets Southport We are your local team of pet care professionals, we are truly ‘passionate about pets’ and we love what we do. We offer a comprehensive range of professional veterinary services to cater for all your pet needs, ranging from preventative health care to weight loss programs through to surgery and diagnostic medicine. Although Greencross Vets is part of a national organisation, our practice is run and managed by a team of dedicated vets, nurses and support staff who understand and value the bond between you and your pet. Our team is committed to offering you and your pet’s exceptional service, and the very best in veterinary medicine and preventative health care. We encourage you to contact us directly should you have any questions about your pet’s health and wellbeing or if you simply want more information about the services that we can provide you and your pets. Our clinic is a new, purpose-built facility in Queen Street Village, with carpark entry available via either Nerang St or Queen St. Book an Appointment Online Our Services. Greencross Vets Southport offer a comprehensive range of professional veterinary services to cater for all your pet care needs utilising the latest diagnostic equipment. View Our Services Desexing Getting your pet desexed (neutered or spayed) is essential to their health. All Greencross Vets facilities are completely sterile and use the latest in surgical equipment. Learn More Vaccinations Prevention is the best medicine. Kitten and puppy vaccinations (injections) and adult pet vaccinations prevent disease. Get your pet’s vaccinations up-to-date. Learn More Heartworm Prevention Heartworm can be hard to detect, but it needn’t be hard to prevent. Greencross Vets recommends year round heartworm prevention. Ask your vet about prevention today. Learn More Dentistry Greencross Vets offer a range of dentistry services like cat and dog teeth cleaning. Consider us your pet’s veterinarian and dentist combined. Learn More X-ray/Radiology Greencross Vets clinics are equipped with high-quality radiograph equipment including X-ray machines, automatic processors, and X-ray view equipment. Learn More Clinical Pathology Clinical pathology allows our vets to analyse and diagnose health conditions. Common laboratory tests include blood tests, urinalysis, faecal tests and biopsy examination. Learn More Laboratory Testing The latest in-house laboratory equipment allows our vets to perform a range of diagnostic tests to achieve accurate, rapid diagnosis of your pets’ health status. Meet The Team Iva Iva Veterinary Nurse Iva completed her Certificate IV in Veterinary Nursing in 2025. Her passion for animal care began in childhood while helping her grandmother care for stray cats in Croatia. This early experience sparked a lifelong dedication to animal welfare, particularly feline care. She has a strong interest in feline nursing, veterinary pathology and emergency care, and aspires to become an emergency Veterinary Nurse. A devoted cat enthusiast, Iva shares her home with four cats—including a lively Bengal—and an American Staffy cross puppy. Outside of her professional pursuits, she enjoys pet sitting and exploring new places on road trips. Melanie W Melanie W Veterinary Nurse Melanie began her career with Greencross Vets in 2023, although her passion for the animal industry began in 2022 when she started fostering cats and kittens. She holds a Certificate IV in Veterinary Nursing and takes great pride in the high standards she sets in her work. Melanie’s professional interests include caring for neonates and overseeing the recovery of hospital and surgical patients. Outside of work, she is a dedicated mother to four boys. Allison Allison Veterinary Nurse Ally is a passionate veterinary technician who graduated from the university of Queensland in 2023. She thrives in fast-paced environments and hopes to pursue a career in emergency. She ensures that every pet receives the highest level of care and making sure your pets get all the love and attention. In her free time, she enjoys traveling and doing outdoor activities. Dr Cian Z Dr Cian Z Veterinarian Dr. Cian grew up in London and returned there after completing his studies to work in a charitable medical practice, where he honed his skills in Emergency Medicine. Relocating to Australia allowed him to transition from the bustling city lifestyle to the tranquility of the beach, all while continuing to dedicate himself to supporting pets and their owners—an opportunity he deeply values. Outside of his professional life, Dr. Cian enjoys long walks, exploring Australia’s natural landscapes, and producing music, in addition to cherishing moments with his beloved cat, Honey. Jessica Jessica Veterinary Nurse Jess’s lifelong love of animals began at a young age while living in the Solomon Islands. She started her nursing career in 2017 with Greencross Gold Coast, working as a locum across various clinics. After taking some time off to focus on her family, Jess was excited to return to working in the clinic. She has a three-legged cat named Mortimor, who is known for being a very cool cat. Dr Taylor A Dr Taylor A Originally from Alaska, Taylor grew up on a small hobby farm. Where she raised a variety of animals from chickens to reindeers. Taylor practiced as an emergency veterinary nurse before making the move to Australia to study for her Doctorate of Veterinary Medicine. She loves the Australian life style and her favourite dogs are Labradors. When she is not at work Taylor likes to spend time with her friends and practice her ukulele. Kirra Kirra Veterinary Nurse Kirra started her journey in the industry when she was in high school, working as a kennel hand in a Townsville based vet clinic. She made the move to the Gold Coast in 2021 and shortly after that she began her studies to become a vet nurse. She is now a Certificate IV Veterinary Nurse and loves all aspects of surgical nursing. When not at the clinic you can find her at the beach or on a long walk with her fur-baby Ruby (Jack Russel). She also loves travelling and exploring the Gold Coast. Dr. John M Dr. John M Veterinary Director Dr. John made the permanent move to the Gold Coast from Durban in South Africa during April 2021 after many years in canine and feline practice. He has a special interest in soft tissue surgery, dentistry, dermatology, pain management and all other aspects of medicine. Dr. John is married to Mareuil and also brought Leah (greyhound cross) and Shimano (whippet) with to the Gold Coast. When not working, he enjoys spending time with family (he has 2 young grandsons) and mountain biking. He appreciates “all things nature” and enjoys birdwatching, hiking, camping and time on the beach. He enjoys being part of the caring Greencross and Southport Team and providing quality care to pets. Anita Anita Veterinary Nurse Anita holds a Certificate IV in Veterinary Nursing and loves all aspects of her job, especially surgical nursing and being an advocate for all fur babies while they stay are patients at Greencross Vets. She likes to keep up to date with best medical practices to ensure that she is always learning and able to provide our patients with exceptional care. When Anita isn’t in clinic, she is busy being a wife and mum to her son, as well as enjoying the company of her fur babies; Eleanor and Shelby. Naomi Naomi Practice Manager Naomi has been working within the Greencross Vets network for a number of years and brings with her a wealth of knowledge about the community. Although she now spends much of her time in an admin and reception role, she continues to love assisting on nursing tasks whenever possible. She especially loves seeing patients go home to their owners after a stay in the clinic. Naomi’s life is filled with animals, her dog Teddy the Staffy who loves to go for walks at the beach, and her two horses Stoka and Sharma. Chloe B Chloe B Veterinary Nurse Chloe began her Vet Nurse training at the young age of 14 through Greencross Vets as school-based trainee and absolutely fell in love with the industry. She has a very strong passion for all aspects of her job, including preventative medicine and having a soft spot for the geriatric patients we see in clinic. Chloe has an older Burmese cat named Leo who loves swimming at the beach with her on the weekends. She currently holds a certificate IV in Veterinary nursing and when she is not in clinic, you can find her surfing, or placed at SeaWorld or Paradise country working with the animals. name: fremantle.wa.gov.au
homepage_content: Fremantle Visitors Centre - City of Fremantle Search the City Clear search field Search filter toggle Search Pages Events Documents News Close search panel Fremantle Visitors Centre The Fremantle Visitor Centre is the official visitor information centre for Fremantle and the true hotspot for visitors to plan their visit. The friendly, experienced staff and ambassadors are local experts and can assist with: Free brochure and maps General tourism information and advice accessibility information guides on events and what’s on free wifi and bike hire information for corporate and conference enquiries Check out the Visit Fremantle website for information about Fremantle including things to do, tours and attractions, hotels and places to stay. Follow @visitfremantle on Facebook , Instagram and Pinterest for all things Fremantle. This facility is accessible. For more information visit the Disability access and inclusion page. Location The Fremantle Visitor Centre is located within Walyalup Koort at 155 High Street, Fremantle. Opening hours Monday to Friday 9am–5pm Saturday 9am–4pm Sunday and public holidays 10am–4pm Closed Good Friday, Christmas Day, and Boxing Day. Fremantle Ambassadors Fremantle Ambassadors are volunteers who provide a friendly face and local knowledge to ensure visitors are able to experience the best Fremantle has to offer. There are three types of ambassadors: Visitor Centre Ambassadors are based at the Fremantle Visitor Centre in Walyalup Koort, 7 days a week, and do a 2.5 hour shift, a least once a week. Roving Ambassadors provide a welcome smile, a map and assistance to visitors at key tourist locations. Roving Ambassadors also play an important role during the cruise ship season (October – April). Roving Ambassadors do a 2 hour shift, at least once a week, 7 days a week. Cruise Ship Ambassadors welcome passengers (during cruise ship season between October and April) from all over the world who are visiting Fremantle for a day (or overnight). Cruise Ship Ambassadors are based at either the Fremantle Passenger Terminal or at the free shuttle stops and do a 2–4-hour shift per cruise ship visit. To become a Fremantle Ambassador, or for more information, please contact the Volunteer Program Officer on 08 9432 9988 or via email at volunteerfvc@fremantle.wa.gov.au Contact us Fremantle Visitor Centre Walyalup Koort, 155 High Street, Fremantle Western Australia 6160 T 08 9432 9988 E info@visitfremantle.com.au Share this page Share on Facebook Share on LinkedIn The City of Fremantle acknowledges the Whadjuk people as the Traditional Owners of the Fremantle/Walyalup area and we recognise their cultural and heritage beliefs are still important today. name: karmateahouse.com
homepage_content: Karma Tea house. Yours Vegan Kitchen Welcome to Karma TEA House Our Productions Explore More Previous Next About Us Karma Tea House Yours Vegan Kitchen Being the best Vegan restaurant in Sydney Karma Tea House, situated on Keira St in Wollongong NSW, stands as a beacon of tradition and health. Embodying the philosophy: "Tea and Vegan dishes bring friends together, forging good bonds atop Wollongong," the establishment came to the city with a mission - to introduce more people to the wonders of Vegan cuisine. Operating on a rigorous schedule, they remain open seven days a week, all year round. At Karma Tea House, meat is strictly off-limits - a testament to their commitment, ensuring guests experience a truly Vegan environment, even barring any outside meat products brought in by customers. Building upon the core essence of Taiwanese Vegan delicacies, after over two years of rigorous experimentation and refinement, the restaurant now proudly showcases a trio of culinary lines: Vegan (VG), Vegan (V, which includes dairy and eggs), and Gluten-Free (GF) - all exuding rich Asian flavors. Additionally, they maintain a strict no-five pungent spices policy in their dishes. Always eager to cater to the local palate, Karma Tea House actively collaborates with local businesses. Through deep partnerships with professional teams, they consistently innovate, introducing dishes that resonate with the local taste. The team passionately hopes to guide more individuals further on their "Vegan journey." Being your second vegan kitch Discover the most comprehensive range of Vegan ingredients and condiments in Australia at Karma Tea House. Catering to the needs of Vegans and those passionate about plant-based diets, we provide an extensive selection to enrich your home cooking experience. Our online store, Karma Sydney Delivery, offers a convenient and hassle-free way to purchase all your Vegan essentials. From novice cooks to seasoned chefs, you'll find everything needed to effortlessly create a variety of Vegan delights. Join us in celebrating the joy of Vegan cuisine and explore the endless possibilities with Karma Tea House. name: laguillotine.com.au
homepage_content: French Restaurant Sydney – La Guillotine French Restaurant/Bistro Tel: 02 9264 1487 / Fax: 02 9264 1428 518 Kent Street, Sydney NSW 2000 laguill@bigpond.com Sydney's finest French restaurant Welcome to La Guillotine French Restaurant/Bistro. One of the oldest French restaurant in Sydney , we are proud to offer a wide range of traditional favourites, daily specials and an exclusive, extensive list of French wines. Ideal for a quick lunch, business lunches, leisurely dinner or special occasion, such as Valentine’s Day and Bastille Day, you will enjoy a wonderful Parisian atmosphere that can be oh-so-romantic. Please call us today for more information and don’t hesitate to ask about party and group bookings. Our history In 1967 La Guillotine opened as a traditional French omelette house in the basement of 9 Albion Place. Now a Sydney icon, our authentic French restaurant first became extremely popular in the 1970s and has hosted many over the years who will never forget the very red walls, the iron bars in the archways and the Parisian atmosphere, emphasised by Edith Piaf and Charles Aznavour playing in the background. In 2002 the restaurant was reborn inside a converted office building at 518 Kent Street, only a stone’s throw away from the old Albion laneway. Current owner Joseph Bradaric, in his 27th year, has expanded the restaurant while keeping the original intimate feeling alive. The ground floor looks down onto Kent Street and takes in the Sydney street life. We hope you will enjoy La Guillotine as others have for many years. Wonderful menu Centrally located in Sydney, our idyllic French restaurant is close to all public transport, parking, the George Street cinemas and Darling Harbour, with disabled access available. Our menus are available in both French and English and include such favourites as: Omelettes Pate Onion soup Escargot Moules marinières Crepes 518 Kent Street Sydney NSW 2000 Tel: 02 9264 1487 Fax: 02 9264 1428 laguill@bigpond.com View our Menu Make a Booking Privacy Policy Share by:

A very extensive and interesting tour, tour guide a retired local who had worked in the mines for 50+ years. His knowledge of the equipment and mining kept everyone interested (including the kids) for the 3 hour tour. A well organised and run tour, highly recommended N Neville GREGORY over 1 year ago Informative and enjoyable underground experience.. Enjoyable and informative experience going underground with a former and knowledgeable miner as guide, who related his experiences and stories during the tour. Gumboots, coveralls and the helmet with a light were definitely required to enjoy the hands-on experiences. What you can expect Gain an insight into the world of mining in Australia with an underground tour of the Hard Times Mine in Outback Mt Isa in Queensland. There is no better way to understand the trials and tribulations of miners than on a guided tour with an ex-miner. Listen to the fascinating stories of the good and hard times deep under the earth plus see how tunnels are formed and shaped below the surface. The Hard Mines Underground tour in Mt Isa also gives participants the opportunity to get up close to machinery and try their hand at the air-leg drill under expert guidance. The underground mine tour is recommended for all people 7 years and above and each person will be provided with safety equipment including overalls, hard hats and gumboots. name: nsw.gov.au
homepage_content: The Big Golden Guitar | NSW Government The Big Golden Guitar The Big Golden Guitar is a replica of the famous Golden Guitar Award and a symbol of the world-renowned annual Tamworth Country Music Festival. Listen About this location Where Corner New England Highway & The Ringers Road, 2 The Ringers Road, Tamworth NSW 2340 Cost Free entry Accessibility Welcomes people with access needs, contact venue/organiser for details Facilities Car park Coach Parking Family Friendly Picnic Area Contact details Email: visittamworth@tamworth.nsw.gov.au Phone: (02) 6767 5300 Request an appointment: https://www.tamworthregion.com.au/operator/big-golden-guitar/ The Big Golden Guitar one of the many "big" attractions in Australia is situated on Goonoo Goonoo Road (New England Highway) at the southern entrance to Tamworth, New. Erected in 1988 and unveiled by Slim Dusty it stands at 12 metres tall and weighs half a tonne. The Big Golden Guitar is a replica of the famous Golden Guitar Award and a symbol of the world-renowned annual Tamworth Country Music Festival. A must see attraction on your visit to Tamworth or merely just passing through The Golden Guitar is available 24hrs and lit at night for the obligatory photograph. homepage_content: Restaurant | Miss Perez Kitchen & Bar | Stirling top of page MISS PEREZ KITCHEN & BAR ABOUT US Miss Perez Kitchen & Bar is situated on one of the prettiest tree-lined street in Stirling. With its contemporary Australian cuisine, Miss Perez prides itself on sourcing local quailty ingredients. The menu draws on cuisines from Latin America, Spain and Australia. Alongside shared plates and more substantial options, there’s a range of burgers – the most notable being the Perez Burger. To drink, there’s local VICE coffee, Adelaide Hills wine and local beers. Floor-to-ceiling windows grant stunning views of Stirling’s iconic oak trees, or you can sit beneath them on the outside deck. Larger groups can gather at the long tables inside, while two smaller rooms provide private nooks for smaller functions and gatherings. homepage_content: Home +61 2 6742 2677 In the heart of the Upper Hunter Valley Home Rooms Check Availability Photo Gallery Location Contact Us Testimonial Welcome to Overlander Motor Lodge We offer a warm friendly traditional country hospitality in Gunnedah north west of NSW. We supply spacious units from 1 person to a family of 5. Units have airconditioning 81 cm wall mounted TV’s, wifi and parking also suitable for trailers. We only use the Australia's best in beds Australian made AH BEARD and still family owned. Rooms have Tea/coffee microwaves, toasters and a good size fridge for those longer stays. Walking distance to the CBD. Our endevour is to use as much Australian produce and products as possible. We look forward to seeing you in the safe travels. Our Facilities WiFi is available in the hotel rooms and is free of charge. Free private parking & secured is possible on site BBQ facilities Room service Family rooms Non-smoking rooms Rooms QUEEN ROOM BOOK NOW TRIPLE ROOM BOOK NOW SMALL FAMILY ROOM BOOK NOW FAMILY ROOM BOOK NOW Check Availability Photo Gallery Location Contact Us Overlander Motor Lodge +61 2 6742 2677 overlandermotel@yahoo.com overlandermotorlodge.com.au 40 Conadilly St, Gunnedah NSW 2380, Australia Enquire With Us Name * Contact No. * Email * Comments & Enquiry * Submit Testimonial Very Happy Travellers "We stayed one night at The Overlander Motel, Gunedah. The owner was very friendly. Our room was spotlessly clean. While the motel is positioned at a busy roundabout it did not affect the quality of our sleep. Only a few blocks from town. We were very happy staying here and would again when back in this town" Great place to stay "The Overlander Motor Lodge, is a nice place to stay. The units are of a good size with a comfortable bed. The unit was very clean and tidy with great shower pressure in the bathrooms. My son and I use the pool the 3 days that we were there. I would recommend the Overlander as we would stay there again. Andrew" Fantastic hospitality. "We were traveling through and decided to stop the night in Gunnedah. We called up and there was only one room left, but it hadn't been cleaned due to a late late checkout. I informed them We have two small children who had been in the car all day so They cleaned it very quickly, the gentleman behind the counter was very accomadating. we were made feel very welcome. The room itself was lovely and spacious. It was very clean and we were the furthest from the road so did not have any noise complaints. I will also add it was one of the most comfortable beds I have ever slept in. Will certainly stay again. The only downside was we ran out of hot water in the morning and the cleaners were a little noisey in the morning." Boris the "Golden Retriever" P.R. Expert "We go tour a lot and we always stay at the Overlander Gunnedah when heading to Moree and Narrabri etc.. it's clean big size rooms have all you need, pool and more! But best of all we stay to be greeted by Boris the dog a golden retriever he is amazing we love him! We stayed 3 nights good price as well. Best comfy bed by far!!!" Food very tasty "We had a very nice queen size room with two comfy armchairs and a table and two chairs. Very comfortable bed, hot shower a good sized flat screen TV on the wall. Parking right outside our door. Mackellar Restaurant is nicely decorated, it's above reception. My husband had fresh oysters and red emperor fish and I had stuffed mushrooms and steak diane, followed by pecan pie. Location is great for travelers but a bit of a walk to centre of town." Good size room, comfortable "Surprisingly a good size room, with 2 x single seater arm chairs. Comfortable bed, wall mounted LCD TV, Tea and coffee facilites, with large mini fridge. Room 12 can be a little noisey, as it is located at the end of the Motel, next to the main road where trucks travel up and down, however this did not affect our sleep quality. Rooms are clean and tidy. Motel is situated on the edge of town, with a 15 minute walk to the main shopping area of Gunnedah. KFC is approx 10 minute walk with McDonalds 20 minutes walk. The Motel also has Fee Wifi (password required from reception), in house resturant and pool. Reception staff are friendly and welcoming." © 2019 - OVERLANDER MOTOR LODGE | Website By Update247 Channel Manager

The Richmond Bakery TASMANIA Long established Bakery/Café Located in the historic and picturesque town of Richmond, Tasmania, the Richmond Bakery have been open since 2000’s. We are renowned for our tasty, hand made Curried Scallop Pie. Must try if you are visiting Tasmania. Opening Hours RICHMOND BAKERY Mon-Fri: 6am-5pm Sat-Sun: 7am-5pm Public Holidays 7am to 5pm Closed on Xmas Day RICHMOND BAKERY ON THE COAST Mon-Fri: 6am-5pm Sat-Sun: 7am-5pm Public Holidays 7am to 5pm Closed on Xmas Day & Good Friday With the great Tasmanian local produce, all of our products are crafted with loads of love and care. All of our products are handmade and made fresh daily, including a wide variety of pies and cakes. We also offer preservative-free bread, salad rolls, and gourmet sandwiches, all served with great coffee. Come visit us and be tempted by our many delicious offerings About us THE TASSIE ICON Curried scallop pies sold here Richmond has lots to offer. Don’t miss out on the great features. Richmond is one of Tasmania’s most popular visitor destinations, showcasing Tasmania and Australia’s colonial heritage at every turn. Heritage-listed buildings and features are found on almost every street, so that even a casual evening stroll offers insights into early settlement days. Know more Find us on Trip Advisor Know more What our customers say about us “ Hands down, the best bakery I've ever been to – and I've been to a lot! The scallop pie and vanilla slice were next level – flaky pastry, so much flavour and a decent size. The old girls on the counter were hilarious – such great service! Highly recommend! Tim Bateup “ They make a fantastic vanilla slice and a really good pepper steak pie, both of which were comparable with the best I had in Tassie. The scallop pie was really good too. There is dining both inside and out and they maintain a busy stream of customers. Wayne T “ With so many delicious looking options making it hard to decide, we finally ordered a Chicken & Camembert pie … The pastry was crisp and fresh, and the filling was delicious … We sat in the courtyard and listened to a nearby harp player (yes, a harp player) while we devoured our morning tea. A very memorable event. Mike Noordermeer “ Best coffee we have had so far in Tasmania was from this bakery! I can see why the vanilla slice has won awards; they have nailed the balance of sweet but not too sweet. Steak pie was amazing! I got one fresh out of the oven. Kaye Eds “ Excellent bakery with all homemade cakes and the quiches are awesome in big or small! The small biscuits are loved by the kids. Really nice outdoor sitting area where the kids can run around and reduce the sugar rush. The coffee is good and the staff is friendly. Lovely stop over in Richmond for a snack or quick lunch! Cintia Tavella Contact Order Coffee THE RICHMOND BAKERY The Richmond Bakery is a well-established bakery and café located in the historic town of Richmond, Tasmania. Known for their famous curried Scallop Pies made with locally sourced produce, the bakery offers both indoor and outdoor seating and is surrounded by beautiful parks. name: vcd.vic.edu.au
homepage_content: Tradeblock Cafe – Victorian College for the Deaf Tradeblock Cafe is an authentic work environment and Deaf space open to the public. Tradeblock offers a hands on hospitality program where senior students experience a range of roles and responsibilities, while contributing to their secondary school qualification. Students are able to build their communication, life skills and understanding of the workplace in a culturally supportive context. The Tradeblock Program assists in breaking down barriers existing around disability. The café is staffed two days a week by senior VCD students, and a post-secondary program operates across another two days. This adult program aims to prepare Deaf people for open employment or further training in the hospitality industry. Those who have participated in work at Tradeblock Cafe identify the benefits this program offers to include increased awareness, skills, confidence, work experience and social networks. There is also benefit to the community who patron the café – other than sustenance, patrons experience Deaf culture and have the opportunity to build their knowledge, awareness and relationships with Deaf people. SBS news “This cafe in Melbourne is run entirely in Australian sign language” Opening Hours Tradeblock Cafe is open during the Victorian school term Tuesdays through to Fridays, 8:30am-2:30pm. Enter via the gate on High Street. The cafe closes for the school holiday periods. Menu Our menu changes daily, and always includes delicious, healthy lunch options and sweet treats. View our sample menu for an idea of what may be available when you come in. To keep updated with news about Tradeblock Cafe (and all the delectable food we’re cooking) follow us on our Instagram page. Catering Tradeblock offers catering services to our local community. You view our catering menu here . For all catering enquiries and bookings, please contact cafe manager Nicole at nicole.mcrae@education.vic.gov.au . Cakes Make your next special occasion even more memorable by ordering one of our Tradeblock celebration cakes. Information regarding pricing and who to contact can be found on our Tradeblock Cake order form . Take a look at our instagram page to see some examples of our work. Lunch Orders All VCD students have access to Tradeblock for lunch and beverages from Tuesdays to Fridays. Primary students order through lunch orders that will be delivered to class, while secondary students may visit the cafe directly to purchase food and drink. homepage_content: Tally Ho Catering – Melbourne's #1 Catering Company Melbourne’s Trusted Catering Partner From boardroom meetings to milestone celebrations, we deliver exceptional catering experiences. With 30+ years of expertise, our professional service makes your event seamless while you focus on what matters most. CONTACT US Melbourne’s Trusted Catering Partner From boardroom meetings to milestone celebrations, we deliver exceptional catering experiences. With 30+ years of expertise, our professional service makes your event seamless while you focus on what matters most. CONTACT US We are Melbourne's No. 1 choice for all your catering needs at affordable prices. Speak to us about catering for your next meeting, event or function. MELBOURNE’S CATERING SPECIALISTS Melbourne's Catering Specialists Tally Ho Catering We are a finger food catering company based in Boronia, delivering party finger food and corporate finger food to all suburbs. If you are looking for finger food catering Melbourne then we can assist you with wide range of fingerfood options including gourmet finger food and sandwich platters to share, as well as party catering, corporate catering and funeral catering. All our finger food is delivered to you tastefully presented and ready to serve. We can also help to provide staff to serve and wait on your behalf and special dietary needs like gluten free catering are not a problem. Since the beginning, Tally Ho Catering has established a strong client base covering a variety of catering requirements and styles. Learn More Cold Food Selection Granola Yoghurt Cups Perfectly portioned in every way! Our breakfast pots have a mix of delicious yoghurt with granola, passionfruit swirl or seasonal fruit salad. Cold Food Selection Peking Duck Asian Pancakes filled with Peking Roast Duck, Cucumber, Celery and tied with a strip of fresh Chives served with a hoisin sauce. Cold Food Selection Rice Paper Rolls Egg noodles, cabbage, carrot & fresh lettuce supplied with a special dipping sauce. Cold Food Selection Roast Beef Blini Rare Roast beef, roasted peppers, tomato chutney and cream cheese on a baby pancakes with fresh chives as a garnish. Hot Food Selection Arancini Italian rice balls that are stuffed, coated with breadcrumbs and deep fried. Hot Food Selection Sausage Rolls Our Homemade Sausage Rolls are a secret family recipe wrapped in crispy puff pastry. Platters Fruit & Cheese Platter Fruit isn't only delicious, it's nutritious too, full of vitamins and antioxidants plus it's very refreshing. A Tally Ho fruit platter is both colourful and appetizing. Sweets Petit Fours Not only do they look wonderful, they taste sensational. Serve with coffee or at afternoon tea, they're completely delectable. Catering Services Our services span a vast array of event types! Tally Ho Catering is sure to meet the requirements for whatever you need. Corporate We believe in good quality catering, high quality service and affordable pricing. Our delicious catering will ensure your guests talk about the food well beyond the event. Learn More Parties Everyone loves a party and having great food that appeals to both kids and adults will ensure that no one goes hungry and your party is a huge success Learn More Funerals Tally Ho Catering have over 30 years of experience catering for families dealing with the loss of a loved one. Our support gives you more time to spend with friends and family. Learn More Occasions Our special occasions catering service guarantees plenty of amazing food to suit everyone’s tastes and requirements at your next event. Let us inspire you! Learn More Our Clients Say... “I just wanted to drop you a note to say thank you for the great experience Amanda and I have had with Tally Ho Catering for an afternoon tea celebrating my parent’s 50th Wedding Anniversary. Your services were recommended to us and we will have no hesitation in using you again and recommending you to others. From the initial enquiry to the delivery of the food, the service and advice from everyone we’ve dealt with has been exceptional. All the guets commented on the quality and presentation of the food, so thank you for helping make the event a success! All the best!” Sunil Daniel, Satisfied Customer “Just a note to thank your Company along with yourself and Maria on the excellent service that you provided us with on Sunday on the occasion of my wife’s special birthday. The food, the content and the presentation, was very well received and as you stated prior to the day when we were discussing quantities with you that the guests would have “plenty” and this was the case. We would like to thank you for your advices and courteous service during the initial stages of planning the event, and your friendly and cheerful service on the day. Once again thank you. Best wishes” Kel Northwood, Satisfied Customer “Hi Team Tally Ho, You looked after the event perfectly and all were very impressed. It was wonderful to see the hospitality you provided to our guests last night. I’m certainly recommending you to everyone I meet, and promoting Tally Ho to all the people at council who order catering. It was a joy to see your skills, expertise and professionalism unfold last night. The food looked beautiful and tasted wonderful, the food and drinks service stream was perfectly timed, and all the staff handled the night with total professionalism and cooperation from start to clean-up. They were well presented, with a caring, respectful attitude and attention to detail that did not go unnoticed. The William and Winifred Bowness Photography prize is the MGA Foundation’s most important and well-known event of the year. You played a major part in its outstanding success.” Amanda Thornton, Program and Operations Co-ordinator Monash Gallery of Art “Just a note to thankyou heaps for the girls on Saturday night, they were fantastic and the food was excellent. Everybody has raved about how good the food was. So a BIG thankyou from us and we will certainly be singing your praises to everbody we know. It was well worth getting you and the girls to do the hard work. Thanks again” Caitlin, Robyn & Steve Livesay, Satisfied Customers “We value and have extensive appreciation from staff re. your catering quality” Deb, CSIRO “I just wanted to say a big thank-you for your service yesterday. The food was great and we have had really good feedback from all of our guests on how nice everything was. Also thank-you for all of your help in the kitchen, you made it so much easier for us to enjoy our daughter’s birthday with our guests than if we tried to do it ourselves! It was really great having you there. All in all, we couldn’t have been happier and wouldn’t hesitate to use your services again!” Nicki McShanag, Satisfied Customer “Hi Vanda I just wanted to thank you for your assistance in ensuring we had a great day for my husband’s birthday on Sunday. You were extremely helpful through the planning phase and the guy who dropped off the food was very friendly. However our biggest thanks to the two ladies who assisted throughout the afternoon – they never stopped – going above and beyond to ensure our guests were completely satisfied. We along with our 90 guests were most impressed with the quality of service provided and also the delicious food. Thank you for making our day great.” Kate, Satisfied Customer “Hi Tally Ho Catering, I just wanted to drop you a quick email regarding a function that was catered for by Tally Ho Catering yesterday. The food and service provided by your company and staff was nothing short of outstanding and you should be congratulated for this. I have kept your business card for future reference.” Allan Chandler, President - Coburg District Football Club “Dear Kathy, I am writing to thank you for the beautiful array of food you prepared for my 80th afternoon tea, birthday party. I really appreciated your advice about the choice of food. The chicken meatballs, the sushi and the cheese and spinach rollinis were very popular amongst all ages. The Petit Fours, the slices and the fruit platter were so attractively displayed and were a great choice, especially popular amongst the young people at the party. It was a very happy day partly due to the fact that the food was all organised and so well accepted. Thank you again. I will contact you again if another occasion arises. With best wishes.” Barbara Craig, Satisfied Customer “I am writing to thank you for helping us so much with our 20th Birthday Luncheon on Wednesday 18th May. The ribbon sandwiches were delicious and also the Petit Fours, we really enjoyed them and the fruit platters were refreshing. The Club Emblem on the Birthday Cake was impressive. Many thanks for all your help.” Gladys Watkins, Hon. Secretary - Probus Ladies Club of Surrey Hills “I just want to thank you for the tremendous job Tally Ho did for us last night. The food was absolutely delicious (and plentiful) and the girls were brilliant – professional, friendly and happy. The function was a huge success and Tally Ho certainly ensured that. Thanks again to you and your team!” Barbara Johnston, Norwood Secondary College “Dear Kathy All the family wanted to say thank you for the catering for Pam’s funeral yesterday morning. It truly was a lovely morning tea, as Pam had instructed and lots of our family and friends commented on how good the catering was. We ended up with nearly a hundred guests attending, so the morning tea really helped the conversations after the funeral service. And with the large number of people who came back the house we got through virtually all of the food by the end of the day. Thank you again for your assistance, and we will certainly bear Tally Ho in mind when any of us are organising functions in the future.” Rob Gebert, Arts Consultancy and Creative Projects “To Kathy and Staff at Tally Ho Catering I would like to express my thanks to yourself and staff for the superb food and service that you supplied on Saturday at my St Vincent De Paul Commendation. My friends and family all commented on your great food and service. Your staff were very pleasant, and if somebody needed something it was not a problem. The kitchen area was also left spotless. Kathy, yourself and staff are to be commended. I will highly recommend Tally Ho Catering to everyone I know.” Annette Burkhalter, Satisfied Customer “Just to let you know that the lunches yesterday were beautiful. Everyone who ordered them thought they were delicious. Once again many thanks. And thanks to the happy young men who delivered them, you must have a great team.” Enid, Monash Region Probus
